\begin{document}$$ \Upsigma ^{2}_{{{\text{DZ}}}} = {\left( {\begin{array}{*{20}c} {{A + C + E}} & {{A/2 + C}} \\ {{A/2 + C}} & {{A + C + E}} \\ \end{array} } \right)} $$\end{document} for the MZ and DZ pairs. Because former analyses showed that a model in which the variance allowed to change linearly during gestational age fitted best (Gielen et al. 2007), we allowed the variance and covariance to change over time (for example, A = eα1 + eα2Time, C = eδ1 + eδ2Time, and ln(E) = σ1 + σ2Time, where Time is gestational age, not time since conception).

